document.title: TEXAS ESSENTIAL KNOWLEDGE AND SKILLS FOR PHYSICAL EDUCATION

2959081CC2384E418F13BFF35D609B75.description: participate in a variety of physical activities in the school and community for personal enjoyment.

89952F4DA3D241558FAED32E4F03051C.description: differentiate among types of and participate in moderate to vigorous physical activities for a sustained period of time on a regular basis using technology when available; and

FFFAFE6669FC400089321EBE53C8D073.description: Lifetime wellness--application of lifetime wellness. The physically literate student identifies the value of lifetime wellness. The student is expected to:

5C82AE7678CC44EFB3254293260B16DB.description: Social and emotional health--accepting and providing constructive feedback. The physically literate student accepts and provides constructive feedback. The student is expected to listen respectfully to make appropriate changes in performance based on feedback from teacher and peers.

889D54553B7449178D4576A2512EA971.description: Social and emotional health--perseverance. The physically literate student perseveres while addressing challenges. The student is expected to identify ways to accept individual challenges and use self-management skills to persevere in a positive manner when learning a variety of new skills.

D632F1B35B4E4727BFA522EC3A2B5FC8.description: demonstrate respect for the feelings of others.

B60974E7A0DB4DB3906CF431E436B617.description: identify effective communication to enhance healthy interactions while settling disagreements; and

762686A745C64148A81522F7D19C03F2.description: discuss ways to resolve conflict in socially acceptable ways and respond to winning and losing with dignity and understanding;

83FF884B0EF541B1892431158829DA1C.description: Social and emotional health--resolving conflict and social interaction. The physically literate student demonstrates competency in resolving conflict and social interaction. The student is expected to:

D2686BD9D3724CF6ACCC614E9CBD3AE7.description: demonstrate self-management skills to control personal impulses and emotions during dynamic activities and lead-up games.

D84921464A64402CBBACB5B0C13CAC9B.description: demonstrate respect for differences and similarities in abilities of self and others; and

E20E78AB30044815B9EE77C9665942C0.description: examine the relationship between nutrition and optimal physical performance; and

53750BB61BCE4E07A1809C3D7AE6C552.description: Health, physical activity, and fitness--nutrition and hydration. The physically literate student recognizes the correlation between nutrition, hydration, and physical activity. The student is expected to:

2720890EE08B4F2C9C944633B14829B1.description: develop personal fitness goals for health-related fitness; and

9C9FDF6F9C6B4BB0ACFDBEFAB65A5A8D.description: Health, physical activity, and fitness--analyze data. The physically literate student demonstrates competency in the ability to analyze data used during fitness performance. The student is expected to:

70ABB082F0364DA4AF97D3EA60797653.description: identify and demonstrate the components of health- and skill-related fitness.

171F952B97A445FE8EB698A3E21E8034.description: demonstrate frequency and intensity during endurance activities; and

0CA0260FFF014ED4B0F77FC2B4D02678.description: describe the benefits of regular physical activity on overall health and wellness;

9231E88D6A6741CAB43FF2FE867BF4B4.description: Health, physical activity, and fitness--fitness principles. The physically literate student demonstrates and recognizes a health-enhancing, physically active lifestyle. The student is expected to:

E49DFBF19A144025A750F26B53AC0264.description: Performance strategies--outdoor and recreational pursuits. The physically literate student demonstrates competency in outdoor and recreational pursuits. The student is expected to participate in a variety of outdoor recreational skills and activities such as camping, backpacking, fishing, rock climbing, hiking, paddle sports, disc golf, cornhole, bocce ball, or croquet.

F229324D30C44E04A916B7468C03117C.description: exhibit appropriate sporting behavior during independent games and activities.

5796D18454D345E7965CD27051738243.description: Performance strategies--games and activities. The physically literate student demonstrates competency in performance strategies in invasion, target, net or wall, fielding, striking, and cooperative games. The student is expected to:

B8D0365094474FF48777582F693F2332.description: Movement patterns and movement skills--rhythmic activities. The physically literate student demonstrates competency in rhythmic activities and rhythmic combinations. The student is expected to demonstrate a rhythmic routine with appropriate steps and movement patterns individually or in a group.

1E2886C149CC4A41AF79E5B493D24922.description: demonstrate appropriate use of pathways and levels during dynamic activities and lead-up games; and

9B716FD561E04720BBAE0316D304F44D.description: demonstrate correct technique in underhand and overhead volleying to a wall, net, or partner;

C5EC337561B548F387EEB145A955685C.description: dribble a ball with control alternating feet while changing both speed and direction with a partner;

768A1B8027D64C818E6B5C850DCB6FFD.description: demonstrate key elements of hand dribbling with dominant and non-dominant hand while changing both speed and direction;

868831BDAB7443D79045A9D4DE3A7748.description: practice the key elements of catching a ball at a variety of levels above and below the waist;

73AD55BD396F42FA8DCEA3E682DB0CDB.description: practice the key elements of manipulative skills, including eye on target, follow-through, body weight transfer, and body position, during dynamic activities;

9A6B7C3A026E4AA291718F2356B260DC.description: Movement patterns and movement skills--manipulative skills. The physically literate student demonstrates competency in developmentally appropriate manipulative skills. The student is expected to:

FA4C99B9CCCA40D3AB6052CD0AD9242F.description: demonstrate and apply correct technique in a variety of locomotor skills during dynamic activities;
